---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Lou Campos - About">
  <main
    class="flex-grow w-full max-w-[1600px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-12 flex flex-col"
  >
    <section
      class="py-12 md:py-24 lg:py-32 w-full border-b border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800 mb-16"
    >
      <div class="max-w-7xl">
        <h2
          class="font-sans font-bold text-3xl md:text-5xl lg:text-7xl leading-[1.1] text-dark-grey dark:text-white tracking-tight"
        >
          Lou Campos (Tokyo, 1988) explores the <span class="text-accent-pink"
            >liminal spaces</span
          > between digital precision and organic chaos.
          <br class="hidden lg:block" />
          His practice deconstructs visual hierarchies to reveal the raw structural
          integrity of memory and form.
        </h2>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-12 lg:gap-20 pb-24">
      <div class="lg:col-span-4 space-y-12">
        <div>
          <h3
            class="font-sans text-sm font-bold tracking-[0.2em] text-dark-grey dark:text-white uppercase mb-8 border-l-2 border-accent-pink pl-4"
          >
            Milestones
          </h3>
          <div
            class="relative pl-4 border-l border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 ml-3"
          >
            <div class="mb-10 ml-6 relative group">
              <a
                class="absolute w-4 h-4 bg-accent-pink rounded-full -left-[41px] top-1.5 border-4 border-white dark:border-background-dark group-hover:scale-125 transition-transform duration-300 ring-2 ring-transparent group-hover:ring-accent-pink/30"
                href="#"></a>
              <a
                class="block group-hover:translate-x-1 transition-transform duration-300"
                href="#"
              >
                <time class="mb-1 text-sm font-sans font-bold text-accent-pink"
                  >2023</time
                >
                <h4
                  class="text-lg font-bold text-dark-grey dark:text-white font-sans group-hover:text-accent-pink transition-colors"
                >
                  "Void &amp; Structure"
                </h4>
                <p
                  class="text-sm font-serif italic text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1"
                >
                  Solo Exhibition, Mori Art Museum, Tokyo
                </p>
              </a>
            </div>
            <div class="mb-10 ml-6 relative group">
              <a
                class="absolute w-4 h-4 bg-accent-pink rounded-full -left-[41px] top-1.5 border-4 border-white dark:border-background-dark group-hover:scale-125 transition-transform duration-300 ring-2 ring-transparent group-hover:ring-accent-pink/30"
                href="#"></a>
              <a
                class="block group-hover:translate-x-1 transition-transform duration-300"
                href="#"
              >
                <time class="mb-1 text-sm font-sans font-bold text-accent-pink"
                  >2021</time
                >
                <h4
                  class="text-lg font-bold text-dark-grey dark:text-white font-sans group-hover:text-accent-pink transition-colors"
                >
                  Luminosity Prize
                </h4>
                <p
                  class="text-sm font-serif italic text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1"
                >
                  Winner, Contemporary Sculpture Category
                </p>
              </a>
            </div>
            <div class="mb-10 ml-6 relative group">
              <a
                class="absolute w-4 h-4 bg-accent-pink rounded-full -left-[41px] top-1.5 border-4 border-white dark:border-background-dark group-hover:scale-125 transition-transform duration-300 ring-2 ring-transparent group-hover:ring-accent-pink/30"
                href="#"></a>
              <a
                class="block group-hover:translate-x-1 transition-transform duration-300"
                href="#"
              >
                <time class="mb-1 text-sm font-sans font-bold text-accent-pink"
                  >2019</time
                >
                <h4
                  class="text-lg font-bold text-dark-grey dark:text-white font-sans group-hover:text-accent-pink transition-colors"
                >
                  "Synthetic Dreams"
                </h4>
                <p
                  class="text-sm font-serif italic text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1"
                >
                  Group Show, White Cube, London
                </p>
              </a>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-6 relative group">
              <a
                class="absolute w-4 h-4 bg-accent-pink rounded-full -left-[41px] top-1.5 border-4 border-white dark:border-background-dark group-hover:scale-125 transition-transform duration-300 ring-2 ring-transparent group-hover:ring-accent-pink/30"
                href="#"></a>
              <a
                class="block group-hover:translate-x-1 transition-transform duration-300"
                href="#"
              >
                <time class="mb-1 text-sm font-sans font-bold text-accent-pink"
                  >2015</time
                >
                <h4
                  class="text-lg font-bold text-dark-grey dark:text-white font-sans group-hover:text-accent-pink transition-colors"
                >
                  MFA, Fine Arts
                </h4>
                <p
                  class="text-sm font-serif italic text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1"
                >
                  Parsons School of Design, New York
                </p>
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3
            class="font-sans text-sm font-bold tracking-[0.2em] text-dark-grey dark:text-white uppercase mb-8 border-l-2 border-accent-pink pl-4"
          >
            Selected Press
          </h3>
          <ul class="space-y-4 font-serif text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
            <li>
              <a
                class="hover:text-accent-pink transition-colors border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 pb-1 block"
                href="#">ArtReview Asia, Winter 2023</a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a
                class="hover:text-accent-pink transition-colors border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 pb-1 block"
                href="#">The Japan Times, "Sculpting Light"</a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a
                class="hover:text-accent-pink transition-colors border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 pb-1 block"
                href="#">Frieze Magazine, Issue 210</a>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="lg:col-span-8 lg:col-start-6">
        <h3
          class="font-sans text-sm font-bold tracking-[0.2em] text-dark-grey dark:text-white uppercase mb-8 hidden lg:block"
        >
          Biography
        </h3>
        <div
          class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert font-serif text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 max-w-none"
        >
          <p>
            Lou Campos is a multidisciplinary artist whose work interrogates the
            relationship between digital architecture and physical presence.
            Born in Tokyo and educated in New York, Campos draws upon a diverse
            cultural lexicon to create minimalist sculptures and installations
            that challenge the viewer's perception of space and volume.
          </p>
          <p>
            His creative process often begins with algorithmic generation, using
            code to identify "errors" or "glitches" in perfect geometric
            systems. These digital anomalies are then meticulously rendered into
            physical reality using traditional materials such as marble, steel,
            and untreated wood. This juxtaposition creates a dialogue between
            the cold precision of technology and the warm, tactile nature of
            craft.
          </p>
          <blockquote
            class="border-l-4 border-accent-pink pl-6 italic text-xl my-8 text-gray-900 dark:text-white"
          >
            "I am interested in the moment a perfect system fails. That fracture
            is where humanity lives."
          </blockquote>
          <p>
            Campos's work has been exhibited internationally, with major
            installations in Tokyo, London, and Berlin. His series <em
              >Structure 01</em
            > was widely acclaimed for its innovative use of light as a structural
            material, creating "walls" that vanish when approached. He continues to
            live and work in Tokyo, where the dense urban landscape serves as a constant
            source of inspiration for his studies on confinement and liberation.
          </p>
          <p>
            Currently, he is developing a new body of work that incorporates
            bio-feedback data to alter the physical shape of kinetic sculptures
            in real-time, further blurring the line between the observer and the
            observed.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-12 pt-12 border-t border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800">
          <a
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 font-sans font-bold text-sm tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-dark-grey dark:text-white hover:text-accent-pink transition-colors group"
            href="#"
          >
            <span>Download Full CV</span>
            <span
              class="material-symbols-outlined text-lg transition-transform group-hover:translate-x-1"
              >arrow_forward</span
            >
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
